vents","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/danielribeiro\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"danielribeiro","type":"User","id":148319,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/danielribeiro\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/danielribeiro\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"NONE","body":"out of interest: is there a way to manipulate all 3 components at the same time (with the current three.js)?\nMathematically I know only this one way (transformation matrix interpolation)\n","created_at":"2013-09-07T07:01:07.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/3848#issuecomment-23983416","id":23983416,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/3848","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIzOTgzNDE2","updated_at":"2013-09-07T08:56:35.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/23983416","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1849512?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mokra","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4NDk1MTI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mokra","type":"User","id":1849512,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Maybe `Matrix4` could have a `lerp` too? ping @WestLangley.\n","created_at":"2013-09-09T19:40:34.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/3848#issuecomment-24108331","id":24108331,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/3848","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI0MTA4MzMx","updated_at":"2013-09-09T19:40:34.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/24108331","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I am not in favor of providing a `lerp` for `Matrix4` if it is going to be used by the user to manipulate the object matrix directly.\n\nSuch a change would require to user to set `object.matrixAutoUpdate = false;` and then call `object.updateMatrixWorld( true );` behind-the-back of the renderer. \n\n`object.matrixAutoUpdate = false;` should only be used if the matrix is static. (ref: #3153)\n\nOn the other hand, we already have\n\n```\nTHREE.Quaternion.slerp( qa, qb, qm, t );\n```\n\nand I could add\n\n```\nTHREE.Vector3.lerp( va, vb, vm, t );\n```\n\nso the user could then use the following pattern to `lerp\/slerp` the `position`, `quaternion` and `scale`.\n\n```\nTHREE.Quaternion.slerp( quatA, quatB, mesh.quaternion, t );\nTHREE.Vector3.lerp( posA, posB, mesh.position, t );\nTHREE.Vector3.lerp( scaleA, scaleB, mesh.scale, t );\n```\n\n@mokra What is your use case for wanting to `lerp` a `Matrix4`? I am always open to compelling arguments.\n","created_at":"2013-09-10T19:30:40.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/3848#issuecomment-24187647","id":24187647,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/3848","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI0MTg3NjQ3","updated_at":"2013-09-10T19:34:51.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/24187647","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"OK, here you go...\n\n```\nTHREE.Vector3.lerp = function ( va, vb, vm, t ) {\n\n    return vm.copy( va ).lerp( vb, t );\n\n}\n```\n","created_at":"2013-09-10T19:41:21.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/3848#issuecomment-24188380","id":24188380,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/3848","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI0MTg4Mzgw","updated_at":"2013-09-10T19:41:21.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/24188380","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":9,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@WestLangley - hi, \nwell I don't have any specific use for now. Though I am doing a lot of experiments with three.js and comparing the mathematics with AS3. In AS3 I often use this Matrix.interpolation, since it provides a very easy and stable way of manipulating the matrix components. If I animate lets say the quaternion and the position at the same time, then (as you can imagine) nothing beautiful comes out. Might it be that the slerp function calculates the quaternions-change linearly ? This should only be done only with the position and the scale.\n","created_at":"2013-09-10T20:24:30.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/3848#issuecomment-24191393","id":24191393,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/3848","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI0MTkxMzkz","updated_at":"2013-09-10T20:24:30.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/24191393","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1849512?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mokra","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4NDk1MTI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mokra","type":"User","id":1849512,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mokra\/orgs"}},{"index":10,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@mokra You definitely need to `slerp` the quaternion. Experiment with my suggestion above and see how it works for you.\n","created_at":"2013-09-10T20:35:54.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/3848#issuecomment-24192213","id":24192213,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/3848","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI0MTkyMjEz","updated_at":"2013-09-10T20:35:54.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/24192213","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.c